                <h1>Understanding Engel v. Vitale: The Landmark Prayer Case</h1>
                <p>Engel v. Vitale was a landmark U.S. Supreme Court case in 1962 that addressed the constitutionality of school-sponsored prayer. The Court ruled that even voluntary prayer, composed by the state, violated the Establishment Clause of the First Amendment. This decision reinforced the separation of church and state in public education.</p>
